      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\t\t \n\n                 \t\n\n\n\t ┬½ All Events\n\n\t\n\tThis event has passed.\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t88 STRINGS: Crossover\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tNovember 4, 2025 @ 7:30 pm - 9:30 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t-\n\t\t\t\t\t\t$10 ŌĆō $42\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tTue Nov 4, 7:30pm | A meeting of musical worlds, 88 Strings is a remarkable Canadian quartet that blends Chinese, Persian, and Western plucked string instruments into a mesmerizing soundscape. Described by one listener as ŌĆ£plucked string heaven,ŌĆØ the ensemble weaves classical, traditional, and newly commissioned works into rich, meditative concerts that feel both ancient and entirely new. Formed through VancouverŌĆÖs Inter-Cultural Orchestra (VICO), the group includes guzheng player Dailin Hsieh, harpist Joy Yeh, tar/setar player and vocalist Ali Razmi, and guitarist/composer John Oliver. Their growing repertoire features original works, global arrangements, and boundary-pushing collaborations with Canadian composers. At the heart of 88 Strings is a deep respect for musical heritage and a shared passion for innovationŌĆöinviting audiences into an immersive listening experience unlike any other.\nBUY TICKETS\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t Details \n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tDate:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t November 4, 2025 \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tTime:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t7:30 pm - 9:30 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tCost:\n\t\t\t\t $10 ŌĆō $42 \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tEvent Category: ArtSpring Presents 2025-26\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWebsite:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t artspring.ca \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\tOrganizer\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tArtSpring\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t Venue \n\t\n\t\t\t\t ArtSpring ŌĆō Theatre \n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t