        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\t\t \n\n                 \t\n\n\n\t ┬½ All Events\n\n\t\n\tThis event has passed.\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\tMET OPERA: I Puritani (Bellini)\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tJanuary 10, 2026 @ 10:00 am - 2:00 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t-\n\t\t\t\t\t\t$15 ŌĆō $25\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSat Jan 10, ┬Ā10am | For gorgeous melody, spellbinding coloratura, and virtuoso vocal fireworks,┬ĀI Puritani┬Āhas few equals. On January 10, the first new Met production of BelliniŌĆÖs final masterpiece in nearly 50 yearsŌĆöa striking staging by Charles Edwards, who makes his company directorial debut after many successes as a set designerŌĆöarrives in cinemas worldwide. The Met has assembled a world-beating quartet of stars, conducted by Marco Armiliato, for the demanding principal roles. Soprano Lisette Oropesa and tenor Lawrence Brownlee are Elvira and Arturo, brought together by love and torn apart by the political rifts of the English Civil War, with baritone Artur Ruci┼äski as Riccardo, betrothed to Elvira against her will, and bass-baritone Christian Van Horn as ElviraŌĆÖs sympathetic uncle, Giorgio. This live cinema transmission is part of the MetŌĆÖs award-winning┬ĀLive in HD┬Āseries, bringing opera to movie theaters across the globe.\n3hr 45 mins | with 1 intermission | Sung in Italian | NEW PRODUCTION\nBUY TICKETS\n┬Ā\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t Details \n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tDate:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t January 10, 2026 \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tTime:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t10:00 am - 2:00 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tCost:\n\t\t\t\t $15 ŌĆō $25 \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tEvent Categories: ArtSpring Presents 2025-26, Metropolitan Opera\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWebsite:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t artspring.ca \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\tOrganizer\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\